\end{align*}Substituting $b = a^2$ and $c = \sqrt{3a}$ into the second equation, we get \begin{align*}
(a^2)^2/\sqrt{3a} &= 2\\
\Rightarrow\qquad a^4 &= 2\sqrt{3a}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad a^4 &= 2a^{3/2}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad a^{4-3/2} &= 2\\
\Rightarrow\qquad a^{7/2} &= 2\\
