Since $X$ and $Y$ are the midpoints of $\overline{BC}$ and $\overline{DA}$ respectively, we have that $XY$ is parallel to $AD$.  Therefore, we can apply the law of cosines to $\triangle AXY$ to obtain
\begin{align*}
XY^2 &= AX^2 + AY^2 - 2AX\cdot AY\cos\theta\\
&= \left(\frac{13}{2}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{24}{2}\right)^2 - 2\cdot\frac{13}{2}\cdot\frac{24}{2}\cos60^\circ\\
&= \frac{169}{4} + \frac{576}{4} - 156\\
&= \boxed{149}.
\end{align*}
